verses.text_plain: Rejoice in the Lord, O ye righteous: for praise is comely for the upright.
verses.verse_html: 1Rejoice in the Lord, O ye righteous: for praise is comely for the upright.

verses.text_plain: Praise the Lord with harp: sing unto him with the psaltery and an instrument of ten strings.
verses.verse_html: 2Praise the Lord with harp: sing unto him with the psaltery and an instrument of ten strings.

verses.text_plain: Sing unto him a new song; play skilfully with a loud noise.
verses.verse_html: 3Sing unto him a new song; play skilfully with a loud noise.

verses.text_plain: For the word of the Lord is right; and all his works are done in truth.
verses.verse_html: 4For the word of the Lord is right; and all his works are done in truth.

verses.text_plain: He loveth righteousness and judgment: the earth is full of the goodness of the Lord.
verses.verse_html:
5He loveth righteousness and judgment: the earth is full of the goodness of the Lord. ▼
▼ goodness: or, mercy

verses.text_plain: By the word of the Lord were the heavens made; and all the host of them by the breath of his mouth.
verses.verse_html: 6By the word of the Lord were the heavens made; and all the host of them by the breath of his mouth.

verses.text_plain: He gathereth the waters of the sea together as an heap: he layeth up the depth in storehouses.
verses.verse_html: 7He gathereth the waters of the sea together as an heap: he layeth up the depth in storehouses.

verses.text_plain: Let all the earth fear the Lord: let all the inhabitants of the world stand in awe of him.
verses.verse_html: 8Let all the earth fear the Lord: let all the inhabitants of the world stand in awe of him.

verses.text_plain: For he spake, and it was done; he commanded, and it stood fast.
verses.verse_html: 9For he spake, and it was done; he commanded, and it stood fast.

verses.text_plain: The Lord bringeth the counsel of the heathen to nought: he maketh the devices of the people of none effect.
verses.verse_html:
10The Lord bringeth the counsel of the heathen to nought: he maketh the devices of the people of none effect. ▼
▼ bringeth: Heb. maketh frustrate

footnotes.body_html: ▼ bringeth: Heb. maketh frustrate

verses.text_plain: The counsel of the Lord standeth for ever, the thoughts of his heart to all generations.
verses.verse_html:
11The counsel of the Lord standeth for ever, the thoughts of his heart to all generations. ▼
▼ to all…: Heb. to generation and generation

footnotes.body_text: ▼ to all…: Heb. to generation and generation
footnotes.body_html: ▼ to all…: Heb. to generation and generation

verses.text_plain: Blessed is the nation whose God is the Lord; and the people whom he hath chosen for his own inheritance.
verses.verse_html: 12Blessed is the nation whose God is the Lord; and the people whom he hath chosen for his own inheritance.

verses.text_plain: The Lord looketh from heaven; he beholdeth all the sons of men.
verses.verse_html: 13The Lord looketh from heaven; he beholdeth all the sons of men.

verses.text_plain: From the place of his habitation he looketh upon all the inhabitants of the earth.
verses.verse_html: 14From the place of his habitation he looketh upon all the inhabitants of the earth.

verses.text_plain: He fashioneth their hearts alike; he considereth all their works.
verses.verse_html: 15He fashioneth their hearts alike; he considereth all their works.

verses.text_plain: There is no king saved by the multitude of an host: a mighty man is not delivered by much strength.
verses.verse_html: 16There is no king saved by the multitude of an host: a mighty man is not delivered by much strength.

verses.text_plain: An horse is a vain thing for safety: neither shall he deliver any by his great strength.
verses.verse_html: 17An horse is a vain thing for safety: neither shall he deliver any by his great strength.

verses.text_plain: Behold, the eye of the Lord is upon them that fear him, upon them that hope in his mercy;
verses.verse_html: 18Behold, the eye of the Lord is upon them that fear him, upon them that hope in his mercy;

verses.text_plain: To deliver their soul from death, and to keep them alive in famine.
verses.verse_html: 19To deliver their soul from death, and to keep them alive in famine.

verses.text_plain: Our soul waiteth for the Lord: he is our help and our shield.
verses.verse_html: 20Our soul waiteth for the Lord: he is our help and our shield.

verses.text_plain: For our heart shall rejoice in him, because we have trusted in his holy name.
verses.verse_html: 21For our heart shall rejoice in him, because we have trusted in his holy name.

tokens.text: in him, because we have trusted

verses.text_plain: Let thy mercy, O Lord, be upon us, according as we hope in thee.
verses.verse_html: 22Let thy mercy, O Lord, be upon us, according as we hope in thee.

tokens.text: be upon us, according as we hope
